Maximum Storage Block in Warehouse Shelves
A warehouse in Chennai stores goods in vertical stacks (histogram form). Each stack has a certain height. The manager wants to find the largest rectangular area that can be formed using consecutive stacks.

This helps identify the maximum storage block that can be allocated efficiently.

Given an array heights[] representing histogram bar heights (each bar has width = 1), find the largest rectangular area that can be formed.
Note: The rectangle must use consecutive bars, and its height is limited by the shortest bar in that range.

Input format :
First line: integer n
Second line: n space-separated integers (heights)
Output format :
Max Area: x

Code constraints :
1 <= n <= 10^5
0 <= heights[i] <= 10^4

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
3
2 4 1
Output 1 :
Max Area: 4
Input 2 :
6
2 1 5 6 2 3
Output 2 :
Max Area: 10



Solution:


 int n = heights.size();

        stack<int>stk;
        heights.push_back(0);

        int max_len = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){

            while(!stk.empty() && heights[i] < heights[stk.top()]){

                int h = heights[stk.top()];
                stk.pop();

                int w = stk.empty()?i:i-stk.top()-1;

                max_len = max(max_len,w * h);
            }

            stk.push(i);
        }

        return max_len;
